  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "If you send a deployment and the transaction reverts, the receipt of that transaction has a non-null `contractAddress`. I don't know if this is intended behavior or if it's a bug.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Send a deployment transaction with this data: `0x6080604052348015600f57600080fd5b506000601a57600080fd5b603f8060276000396000f3fe6080604052600080fdfea2646970667358221220e30f63f383b7791836a8f2022e0baac71c054a6385e97dd23846be98a2dcceb364736f6c63430008110033`. This is just an empty contract whose constructor only has a `require(false);` statement.\r\n2. Get the receipt of this transaction. The `status` should be 0, but you'll see that there is a non-null `contractAddress`.\r\n3. Get the code of that address. It should be `0x`.",
